 <Description>
<![CDATA[
 This program uses the frame burst API to aggregate multiple frames into each
 grab command. The total number of acquired frames per grab command issued is
 tabulated and the results are shown on screen.<br /><br />
 This API is useful when acquiring from high frame rate cameras that might
 cause frames to be lost if they are grabbed only one frame at a time.<br /><br />
 The end of the grab can be signaled by up to 3 events:<br />
 1: an external signal has triggered the end of frame aggregation;<br />
 2: the frame aggregation count has been reached;<br />
 3: the maximum aggregation time has elapsed.<br />
]]>
</Description>
